'''Antenor Orrego Espinoza''' (22 May 1892 – 17 July 1960) was a [[Demographics of Peru|Peruvian]] writer and [[political philosopher]]<ref name="Pakkasvirta"/> of [[Basque people|Basque]] ancestry.  He was a member of the [[American Popular Revolutionary Alliance]] (APRA).  The [[Antenor Orrego Private University|Universidad Privada Antenor Orreg]]o (Antenor Orrego Private University), founded in [[Trujillo, Peru]] in 1988, is named for him.<ref name="University"/>

Antenor Orrego was born in 1892 to José Asunción Orrego and Victoria Espinoza Villanueva in the [[Santa Cruz Province, Peru|Santa Cruz Province]] of the [[Cajamarca Region]] of [[Peru]].  He died in [[Lima]], [[Peru]] in 1960.<ref name="Amauta"/>

