'''David Chadwick''' (born 1945) grew up in [[Texas]] and moved to [[California]] to study [[Zen]] as a student of [[Shunryu Suzuki]] in 1966.  Chadwick was [[ordained]] as a [[Buddhism|Buddhist]] priest in 1971, shortly before Suzuki's death.  He assisted in the operation of the [[San Francisco Zen Center]] for a number of years.

Chadwick has two children and has married and remarried.  He has written several books and continues to "dabble in Buddhism and related matters".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cuke.com/dchad%20misc/dchad.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2004-10-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041010024255/http://www.cuke.com/dchad%20misc/dchad.html |archivedate=2004-10-10 |df= }}</ref>  Among his works is ''Crooked Cucumber'', the biography of Shunryu Suzuki.

