'''''Kris''''' (meaning Crisis in English) was a culture magazine published in Sweden. It existed from 1975 to 1997.
==History and profile== The magazine was established by [[Stig Larsson (author)|Stig Larsson]] and [[Åke Sandgren]] in [[Umeå]] in 1975.<ref name="ron">{{cite web|title=The Journal Crisis|url=https://translate.google.com.tr/translate?hl=en&sl=sv&u=http://ronnells.se/tidskriftensirk/&prev=search|work=Rönnells|accessdate=22 May 2016}}</ref> It was first named ''CODE'' and it was renamed as ''Kris'' in 1977.<ref name="ron"/> The magazine was published between 1977 and 1997 by Föreningen KRIS.<ref name=ne.se>[http://www.ne.se/uppslagsverk/encyklopedi/lång/kris-(tidskrift) Kris tidskrift] Retrieved 22 May 2016.</ref>
The magazine featured articles on critique, philosophy and æsthetics.<ref name="ne.se"/> [[Horace Engdahl]] and [[Anders Olsson (writer)|Anders Olsson]] were part of the editorial staff.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fokus.se/2011/09/sanningssagaren-stig/|title=Sanningssägaren Stig|work=Fokus|date=September 2011}}</ref>
